{
  "stem": "4284.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "And when we finally did get out and managed to creep, and I do mean creep, they said, welcome to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "And I was back in Germany-- made one incredible round trip.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "Buchenwald had been a facility that, that was sort of the privileged camp for political prisoners, for many, many German prisoners that had criminal records, political prisoners from other countries, Leon Blum from, you know, from France, who was Jewish was there, and so on.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 89,
      "text": "And there wasn't the direct killing going on when I arrived, because it was near the end the war.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 90,
      "text": "You did have, of course, thousands of people die-- hundreds basically each day by, I guess you might say, for, for choice of a better word, attrition.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 91,
      "text": "It's all, of course, malnutrition, rather than systematic killing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 92,
      "text": "That had already kind of stopped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 93,
      "text": "We did have the infamous Ilse Koch, who was the commandant's wife, riding through the camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 94,
      "text": "And she was responsible for tattooed skins being made into lampshades.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 95,
      "text": "And you do have the specimen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 96,
      "text": "And they do have the shrunken heads.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 97,
      "text": "These things were still going on to a lesser degree, because we didn't know that Germany had been invaded, that Europe had even been invaded by the Allies.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 98,
      "text": "We had no such information.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 99,
      "text": "And from January to April, without going through the atrocities would say that the Germans did as a last act in trying to destroy the camp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 100,
      "text": "We waited and had no activities, very little food.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 101,
      "text": "Most of us did recover from the little bread that they gave us to sustain us sufficiently.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 102,
      "text": "And then, for reasons that we did not know, we heard rumbling.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 103,
      "text": "We heard noise.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
